This paper is primarily focused on privacy and security in web browsing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the performance benefits of the technology, which could potentially fall under web technologies (cs.WEB) or systems and networking (cs.SI). The evaluation of the approach involves analyzing data usage and page load time, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
